{"questionId":"33230281","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The time, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi></math> minutes, taken to complete a jigsaw puzzle can be modelled by a normal&nbsp;distribution with mean <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>μ</mi></math> and standard deviation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>It is found that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>30</mn><mo>%</mo></math>&nbsp;of times taken to complete the jigsaw puzzle are longer than&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>36</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn></math>&nbsp;minutes.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Use&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>μ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>32</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>29</mn></math> in the remainder of the question.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>86</mn></math>th percentile time to complete the jigsaw puzzle.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>t</mi><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>86</mn></mrow></msub></math> be the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>86</mn></math>th percentile</p>\n<p>attempts to use the inverse normal feature of a GDC to find <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>t</mi><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>86</mn></mrow></msub></math> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>(M1)</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>t</mi><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>86</mn></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>41</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn></math> (mins)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>A1</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>[2</strong><strong>&nbsp;marks]</strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"33230281","referenceCode":"EXN.2.SL.TZ0.8b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the 86th percentile time to complete the jigsaw puzzle.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.9—Normal distribution and calculations","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.12—Z values, inverse normal to find mean and standard deviation"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}